  "notes": "©  ℗ 1980 De-Lite Recorded Sound Corp.\n\n[l294000] - Number code on labels: 53. In 1974 a new two-step pressing ring was adopted; the shouldered outer ring measured ~ 2.75\" and the inner ring measured 1.1875\".  The company \n                  lasted until mid 1981 when it became Hauppauge Record Manufacturing Ltd.  This Album was © & ℗ 1980.\n\n[l199325] - The mastering stamp usually takes the form of MASTERING BY FRANKFORD/WAYNE NEW YORK, or the initials F/W followed by an apple symbol. \"F/WTC\" = Tom Coyne\n\nBand name DOES NOT appear on labels.\n\nRecorded at House Of Music.\nMastered at Frankford Wayne.\n\nWe dedicate this music to the people. Come and celebrate the next step in the career of Kool And The Gang. We love you.",
